6:
*sigh* Just how far is this place? I'm
about to pass out already...
10:
Did you not say you wished to come
here no matter what? You certainly
do tire easily...
15:
Give me a break. I'm an intellect... I
can't do much unless I'm drowning
in sweets...
20:
Here, I happen to have a piece of
candy.
25:
C'mon, we need to get a move on!
Hurry it up!
29:
Here it is—the pattern I mentioned
having seen before!
38:
Just as I thought... Magic theory is
written on it.
41: You're capable of reading it, Nellie?
44:
Not all of it. And the parts I CAN
make out are a bit vague, but I can
get the basic gist of it.
49: Not bad... So tell us what it says.
55:
It basically explains the concept
behind summoning familiars, but...
65:
It's usable only by someone with
access permissions.
70:
You mean it's not something you
would be able to use?
81:
Psh, now you're just leaving us
hanging.
84:
Like I said, I can get the gist of it. And
if we add what I know about magic
theory...
96: Wh-what the heck did you just do?!
100:
The spell seemed doable with a bit
of modification...
104: So I went ahead and did just that!
109:
Nellie... Please tell me you can stop
that thing.
113: Stop it? Er, I don't know about that...
123:
I might be a genius, but I can only
do so much without full access
permissions. If I could just research
this for a few years—
127: Uh-oh, my body's out of sugar...
133: You've gotta be yanking my tail!
138:
Um... Things don't look too good, do
they?
143:
Stella, get Nellie out of here. We'll
deal with the golem.
149:
I-I'm not leaving just yet! I'M the one
who activated the thing, and I have
to take responsibility!
152:
Don't count my magic theory out
just yet! I might not be able to take
full control of the golem, but I can at
least delay its actions!
156: Oh yeah? Do your thing then!
161:
Um, let's see... Given the conceptual
theory behind automaton familiar
types—
165:
No, wait! I only have to DELAY the
thing, so there's no need to overtake
its central control system! If I can
just disrupt its driving mechanisms—
169:
Crud, I'd need mana to do that!
There must be some other way!
176:
I believe in you. Here's a piece of
candy.
185:
Thankfully, I'm not COMPLETELY
mana-less! With a bit of magic
theory, sophistication, guts...
188: And sugar, I've got this covered!
195:
Ehehe... I did it... I actually used
magic...
199:
Phew... We're gonna have it rough if
Nellie's gonna need forty winks after
every spell she casts.
205:
You have to admit that was a huge
jump from not being able to use
magic at all though.
210:
Yeah, I'll give her credit where
credit's due.
222:
Heh... No stopping that one-track
mind of hers.
